    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.117-119_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">117</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Sioux City 3. Iowa
                        June 26. 1958
                    </dateline>

                    <salute>Dear Dr Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I recieved a letter today from Mrs Bower Aly telling me for the first time of the death of Mrs Neihardt I had not heard of it before and am so sorry to be so late in writing to you. I think I can appreciate somewhat as to how much she is missed both by you and the children. I shall always remember her as a very dear and good friend.</p>
                
                <p>I do not go over to Wayne very often&#8212;Too bad there are so many interests that, at the time seem so important to keep one from keeping in touch with old friends. I did go over around the first of May to attend a dinner honoring three faculty members who are retiring this summer &#8212; They were in Wayne all the time I had been there&#8212;one of them is Mr <hi rend="caps"><unclear>JS.</unclear></hi> Owen, head of the English department.
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.117-119_0002"/>
                    
                <fw type="curatorial">118</fw>
                
                    You may remember him. They plan to sell their home and go to a warmer climate and, I think, to be near their daughter and grand-children.</p>
                
                <p>There are so many changes at Wayne&#8212;so many new faces on the faculty, another new president and also many new buildings. The college is growing rapidly.</p>
                
                <p>I keep busy &#8212; have a part time job with a bookkeeping and tax services man&#8212;Have plenty to do during the income tax return season but, after that, work only half a month and four hour a day &#8212; That with my housework keeps me <unclear>fairly</unclear> well occupied.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With sincere sympathy</salute>
                
                    <signed>Mildred Piper</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
